WEBVTT

00:04.372 --> 00:06.440
CHRIS ROCK:
When I was 14,

00:06.474 --> 00:08.676
it seemed like
all I did was work.

00:08.709 --> 00:11.579
I worked at school.

00:11.612 --> 00:13.481
* We're not scared
to lose at all *

00:13.514 --> 00:15.283
* Security throw
through the wall *

00:15.316 --> 00:17.351
"Four score and seven years ago,
our forefathers

00:17.385 --> 00:19.520
"brought forth from this
continent a new nation,

00:19.553 --> 00:22.090
"conceived in liberty and
dedicated to the proposition

00:22.123 --> 00:23.624
that all men are created equal."

00:23.657 --> 00:25.659
I worked at home.

00:25.693 --> 00:29.397
* Unless we're clinging
to the things we prize *

00:29.430 --> 00:33.601
* And do you feel scared?
I do *

00:33.634 --> 00:37.471
Sometimes I even
went sleep-working.

00:37.505 --> 00:43.277
* And if we threw it all away

00:43.311 --> 00:46.547
* Things can only get better

00:48.449 --> 00:52.820
But the one thing I always did
for fun was go to the movies.

00:52.853 --> 00:55.256
Man, did you see Purple Rain?

00:55.289 --> 00:56.757
Yes!

00:56.790 --> 00:58.592
"Why don't you stay awhile,
see how it's done?"

01:00.661 --> 01:01.762
Man, did you see Rambo?

01:01.795 --> 01:03.597
Yeah.

01:03.631 --> 01:05.533
"Do we get to win
this time, sir?"

01:06.667 --> 01:08.702
Man, did you see
Beverly Hills Cop?

01:11.239 --> 01:14.342
"Here, why don't you go
ahead and take this banana?"

01:14.375 --> 01:17.578
The one big movie I missed
was Ghostbusters.

01:17.611 --> 01:19.380
"I got slimed."

01:19.413 --> 01:20.881
"Man, that chick is toast."

01:20.914 --> 01:22.883
Are they still talking
about Ghostbusters?

01:22.916 --> 01:25.553
Yeah. It's only the biggest
movie out this year.

01:25.586 --> 01:27.288
I can't believe
you haven't seen it.

01:27.321 --> 01:28.522
Have you seen it?
No.

01:28.556 --> 01:30.158
Well, then what are
you talking about?

01:30.191 --> 01:31.159
I thought you
saw everything.

01:31.192 --> 01:32.460
I kept missing it.

01:32.493 --> 01:34.162
Now the only place
it's still playing

01:34.195 --> 01:35.229
is the dollar theater.

01:35.263 --> 01:36.797
But popcorn still
cost eight bucks.

01:36.830 --> 01:38.632
And this is the last week.

01:38.666 --> 01:40.168
Maybe we can
catch it on Saturday.

01:40.201 --> 01:41.369
It leaves Thursday.
Forget it.

01:41.402 --> 01:42.836
We'll just have
to see it

01:42.870 --> 01:44.672
when it comes out on
video in four years.

01:44.705 --> 01:45.873
Back then, that was quick.

01:45.906 --> 01:47.841
I'm not waiting four years.

01:47.875 --> 01:50.778
Class...

01:50.811 --> 01:51.612
I just want to let you know
that I won't be here tomorrow

01:51.645 --> 01:53.547
because I have
a funeral to attend.

01:53.581 --> 01:55.249
Who died?

01:55.283 --> 01:57.818
My sister.

01:57.851 --> 01:59.353
Oh, I'm sorry.

01:59.387 --> 02:00.621
Thank you, Chris.

02:00.654 --> 02:02.923
It's hard because I don't have

02:02.956 --> 02:05.759
19 or 20 other siblings
like you.

02:07.528 --> 02:09.397
What'd she die of?

02:09.430 --> 02:11.532
She died of a bad case
of grammar.

02:12.733 --> 02:16.170
Watch those prepositions.

02:16.204 --> 02:17.905
Greg, you know what?

02:17.938 --> 02:20.274
I think we can go
see this movie.

02:20.308 --> 02:22.343
Well, how are we
going to do that?

02:22.376 --> 02:23.711
Cut school.

02:23.744 --> 02:26.214
I ain't afraid of no ghosts.

02:34.322 --> 02:36.290
* Aw, make it funky now!

